	   <tr><td colspan=2>let's be honest a hybrids wis/int or mana doesn't really matter too much in a raid or in most battles where there is a caster present.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not to say that their spells don't matter but does two extra 100 dmg nukes when ppl are casting nukes in the 1000s?  The strength is very nice for any meleer but it is a catch 22 because the meleers should be darn high on their strength already and with delay and haste from other items in the game in this slot it isn't as worth it.  As far as int casters....well let's just say this int casters have near 50 int from there hands/range slots alone would be serious overkill for 20 more.  This is an ideal item for clerics, druids, and shammies.  as far as clerics and druids i don't know 1 druid that doesn't get encumbered after a half hour of fighting especially if it's one of those less choosen paths of an erudite gnome or dark elf.  druids never have decent ac items and have even worse for resistance items.  druids aren't made to be hit but when you fight summoning creatures it because apparent you definitely will be.  and although i really like the monk class quit plugging any 1 or lower weight item as yours its pretty annoying.  it's a great item for all classes.  but seeing that most meleers don't get a good boost from 20wis/int and 75mana i wouldn't choose to give it to them.  If i was a raid leader i figure the guild as a whole would benefit from it going to a cleric first, druid second, shamman third(hp cannabling), enchanter fourth, rogue 5, monk 6, rest of ints, hybrids, then the rest of meleers at the end.  But if you ever have a rogue or monk getting this item let me know i want to join your guild because you've obviously gotten enough of these to go around ;-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
